      "writtenOn": "2017-08-04T18:01:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed. I would not delete from GS at all, but instead remove runs we are not interested in \nfrom the result store. The GS data essentially fall by the wayside by not being re-ingested. \nWe have had really good success by essentially treating GS as immutable data and only deleting files there in exceptional situations. Everything else can be re-calculated from the GS data if necessary. \n\nThe pattern for background cleanup processes has been to create a go-routine that does periodic cleanup and has a Liveness metric to make sure it doesn\u0027t die.",
